| Wolfram Offers Prize For (2,3) Turing Machine                      |
|   from the universal-or-not dept.                                  |
|   posted by kdawson on Wednesday May 16, @02:53 (Math)             |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/15/2253218      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Stephen Wolfram, creator of Mathematica and
author of [0]A New Kind of Science, is offering a [1]prize of $25K to
anyone who can prove or disprove his conjecture that a particular
2-state, 3-color Turing machine is universal. If true, it would be the
simplest universal TM, and possibly the simplest universal computational
system. The announcement comes on the 5-year anniversary of the
publication of NKS, where among other things Wolfram introduced the
[2]current reigning TM champion — 'rule 110,' with 2 states and 5
colors."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/15/2253218

