Bananatree3 writes "Popular Icelandic photographer and art-student
[0]Rebekka Guoleifsdottir has been targeted by Flickr [1]for posting a
plea for help in a theft case involving an online retailer selling
copycat art. She requested that people send the retailer letters
concerning the issue, and in response [2]her original post was promptly
deleted. It is still ironically [3]available on Yahoo cache. In the end
it appears that the retailer had been duped by a rogue art dealer under
the title [4]"Wild Aspects and Panoramics LTD". However, Flickr seems to
have overstepped its bounds in deleting this post." This whole case
brings back up the messy issues surrounding content ownership in this
strange new world of a services based internet.

