+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Frequent Slashdot Contributor [0]Bennett Haselton's latest story is ready
for your consumption. He starts "Recently, as an experiment, I wrote from
my Hotmail account to ten different hosting companies that were each
hosting some of my Web sites, asking for logins to change the domain
settings. Even though I never provided any proof that the messages from
the Hotmail account were really coming from me (the address they all had
on file for me was a different one), half of them replied back and gave
me the logins that I needed."

